.TH WindowMenuSelect 3X
.SH NAME
\*LWindowMenuSelect \*O\(em Command to select an item from the window menu
.SH SYNOPSIS
\*LWindowMenuSelect\*O
\*Vwidgetname <ItemName | ItemNum>\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
\*LWindowMenuSelect\*O
command will select the menu item specified by
\*VItemName\*O or
\*VItemNum\*O
from the window menu on the window associated with
\*Vwidgetname\*O.
If
\*Vwidgetname\*O
is not a shell with its own window on the display, the window
of the nearest shell parent in the widget hierarchy will be used.
This function is executed by moving the pointer down the systemMenu
to the item specified and generating a Select button click.
If the selected item is insensitive, a warning will be printed and
the menu unposted.
.IP "\*Vwidgetname\*O" 14n
The XtName of the widget to be acted upon.
.IP "\*VItemName\*O" 14n
Name of the item in the menu you wish to select.
.IP "\*VItemNum\*O" 14n
Number in the menu corresponding to the item you wish to select.
.PP
For more information about \*LWindowMenuSelect\*O, see
the \*EOSF/Motif Quality Assurance Test Suite User's Guide\*O.
.SH EXAMPLE
\*LWindowMenuSelect Shell1 Lower\*O
.PP
This command will move the pointer to the item \*LLower\*O in the
window menu of the window associated with \*LShell1\*O, and select it.
.PP
\*LWindowMenuSelect Shell1 3\*O
.PP
This command will move the pointer to item number 3 of the window menu
of the window associated with \*LShell1\*O, and select it.
.SH NOTE
\*EIn version 1.2, items \*LMove\*E and \*LSize\*E
are removed from the window menu.
However, the corresponding operations are provided through the commands
\*LWindowMove\*E and \*LWindowResize\*E respectively\*O.
